{\par \b Syntax:}\par segment(Point1, Point2)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Draws a segment defined by its endpoints.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par segment(1+2i, 4) draws the segment defined by the points whose coordinates are (1, 2) and (4, 0).\par segment(GA, GB) draws segment AB.\par }